cpplib provides CMake targets:

```cmake
find_package(cpplib CONFIG REQUIRED)
target_link_libraries(main PRIVATE cpplib::cpplib)
```

The package provides a C++ utility library with:

- String formatting and logging using fmt
- Mathematical utility functions
- Cross-platform static/dynamic library support

Example usage:

```cpp
#include <cpplib/cpplib.h>

int main() {
    cpplib::StringFormatter formatter;
    formatter.log("INFO", "Hello, {}!", "World");

    auto fib = cpplib::MathUtils::fibonacci(10);
    return 0;
}
```
